Saved!
Job Details
SCHOOL ADMINISTRATION POST. SSAT (Middle East) is a well-respected Consultancy, working with a large educational foundation to open a new school in Mohammed Bin Zayed City, to start in September 2014. We are seeking staff members to start work with us from early May. Applicants should send their CV, a photograph, current salary, and the names and contact details of 2 referees to: hr2@ssat.me by Monday, 5th May. State the position you are applying for in the subject line of your email. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted, and responses will be made as CVs are received. SSAT Website: www.ssat.me | The language used in the administration will be English.Site Manager - The School Site Manager will supervise the work of the school contractors in all areas. This senior position requires a minimum of 10 years of experience in a similar role, preferably in a school. The Manager will lead and manage teams and will need to demonstrate this experience. Reporting demands a high level of written and spoken English but spoken Arabic is also important. Start June.Applicants should send their CV, a photograph, current salary, and the names and contact details of 2 referees to: hr2@ssat.me by Monday, 5th May. State the position you are applying for in the subject line of your email. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted, and responses will be made as CVs are received. SSAT Website: www.ssat.me
